# Mobile App Build Context (mobile-app-docs)

The **NCS Employee Mobile App** and all related backend work are built **according to the mobile-app-docs** in this repo.

## Source of truth

- **`mobile-app-docs/NCS_EMPLOYEE_MOBILE_APP_README.md`** — Full development plan, features, API endpoints, notification catalog, screen breakdown, phases.
- **`mobile-app-docs/MOBILE_APP_INTEGRATION_README.md`** — API base URL, auth (Sanctum), headers, push (Expo), CORS.
- **`mobile-app-docs/API_GAPS_IMPLEMENTED.md`** — Backend API gaps already implemented for mobile.

## Key constraints

1. **Notifications:** Every notification that fires on the web MUST also fire as a push notification on the mobile app (Expo Push). An observer on `Notification` (`App\Observers\NotificationObserver`) dispatches `SendExpoPushNotificationJob` on every `Notification::created()` when the user has a valid Expo `push_token` — so all code paths that create notifications (not only `NotificationService::notify()`) trigger push.
2. **API prefix:** Mobile API lives under `/api/v1/` (or configured mobile prefix). Auth: Sanctum Bearer token; login accepts optional `push_token`; register-token: `POST /notifications/register-token`.
3. **Expo push:** Backend sends push via Expo Push API (`https://exp.host/--/api/v2/push/send`), not FCM/APNs directly. Token format: `ExponentPushToken[...]`.
4. **Features and phases:** Follow the feature list and development phases in NCS_EMPLOYEE_MOBILE_APP_README.md (Auth → Profile → Pass/Leave → Emolument → Chat → Notifications → Transport, etc.).

When adding or changing mobile-related backend (API, notifications, push), check mobile-app-docs first and keep behavior aligned with these specs.
